wikipedia_page.main: Liam Corr (born 19 June 1990) is a Scottish former professional footballer. Corr now works at Falkirk as their Retail and Ticketing Manager.

response: Molloy went on loan to Second Division side Stirling Albion on 18 September 2008, until the end of December after Stirling lost both John O'Neill and Liam Corr to injury. Molloy had also been on loan at Forthbank towards the end of the previous season as well.
